data.chText: 鞭子
data.enText: a long thin piece of rope or leather, attached to a handle, used for making animals move or punishing people

data.chText: 他甩了个响鞭，马儿就奋蹄向前奔去。
data.enText: He cracked his whip and the horse leapt forward.

data.chText: 纪律委员，组织秘书（在政党中负责确保党员出席政府重要辩论并表决）
data.enText: an official in a political party who is responsible for making sure that party members attend and vote in important government debates

data.chText: 组织秘书长
data.enText: the chief whip

data.chText: （政党发给党员的）投票通知书，投票指示
data.enText: a written instruction telling members of a political party how to vote on a particular issue

data.chText: 搅打奶油甜食（用奶油、鸡蛋、糖和水果搅打而成）
data.enText: a sweet dish made from cream, eggs, sugar and fruit mixed together
have/hold, etc. the whip hand (over sb/sth)

data.chText: 执掌大权；执鞭在手
data.enText: to be in a position where you have power or control over sb/sth
crack the whip

data.chText: 极度役使
data.enText: to use your authority or power to make sb work very hard, usually by treating them in a strict way
a fair crack of the whip

data.chText: （做某事的）合理机会
data.enText: a reasonable opportunity to show that you can do sth

data.chText: 我觉得我们没有得到合理的机会。
data.enText: I felt we weren't given a fair crack of the whip.

data.chText: 鞭打；鞭策；以鞭打责罚；鞭笞
data.enText: to hit a person or an animal hard with a whip , as a punishment or to make them go faster or work harder

data.chText: （使朝某一方向）猛然移动
data.enText: to move, or make sth move, quickly and suddenly or violently in a particular direction

data.chText: 一条树枝突然划过车窗。
data.enText: A branch whipped across the car window.

data.chText: 她的头发随风在脸际飘拂。
data.enText: Her hair whipped around her face in the wind.

data.chText: 时速50英里的大风卷起了波浪。
data.enText: The waves were being whipped by 50 mile an hour winds.

data.chText: （突然迅速地）除去，拉动，抽出
data.enText: to remove or pull sth quickly and suddenly

data.chText: 她刷地一下子把脸上的面具摘掉了。
data.enText: She whipped the mask off her face.

data.chText: 那个人突然抽出一把刀来。
data.enText: The man whipped out a knife.

data.chText: 搅打（奶油等）
data.enText: to stir cream, etc. very quickly until it becomes stiff

data.chText: 端上加了搅打奶油的馅饼。
data.enText: Serve the pie with whipped cream .

data.chText: 把蛋白打得起稠尖儿。
data.enText: Whip the egg whites up into stiff peaks.

data.chText: 偷；盗窃
data.enText: to steal sth
whip through sth

data.chText: 匆匆做；迅速完成
data.enText: to do or finish sth very quickly

data.chText: 我们十分钟便办完了海关手续。
data.enText: We whipped through customs in ten minutes.
whip sb/sth↔up

data.chText: 激发；激励；煽动
data.enText: to deliberately try and make people excited or feel strongly about sth

data.chText: 这些广告是为了激起公众的舆论。
data.enText: The advertisements were designed to whip up public opinion.

data.chText: 他是个真正有感召力的演说者。
data.enText: He was a speaker who could really whip up a crowd .

data.chText: 匆匆做（饭等）
data.enText: to quickly make a meal or sth to eat

data.chText: 她用了15分钟就给我们备好了一顿可口的午餐。
data.enText: She whipped up a delicious lunch for us in 15 minutes.

trans: 激起，煽动（仇恨等危险情感）

tr: a quick blow delivered with a whip or whiplike object
example: the whip raised a red welt

tr: an instrument with a handle and a flexible lash that is used for whipping
(golf) the flexibility of the shaft of a golf club
a dessert made of sugar and stiffly beaten egg whites or cream and usually flavored with fruit
a legislator appointed by the party to enforce discipline

example: The Senator blistered the administration in his speech on Friday
He mopped up the floor with his opponents

tr: beat severely with a whip or rod
example: The teacher often flogged the students

tr: whip with or as if with a wire whisk
thrash about flexibly in the manner of a whiplash
example: The tall grass whipped in the wind

value.def: A whip is a long thin piece of material such as leather or rope, fastened to a stiff handle. It is used for hitting people or animals.
If someone whips a person or animal, they beat them or hit them with a whip or something like a whip.

example.ex: Eyewitnesses claimed Mr Melton whipped the horse up to 16 times...
example.tran: 目击证人称梅尔顿先生抽打了这匹马16鞭之多。

example.ex: He was whipped with a studded belt.
example.tran: 他被用带有饰钉的皮带抽打。

example.ex: He threatened to give her a whipping.

value.def: If something, for example the wind, whips something, it strikes it sharply.

example.ex: A terrible wind whipped our faces...
A branch whipped her across the cheek.
example.tran: 一根树枝抽打到了她的脸颊。

value.def: If something flexible whips in a particular way, it moves sharply when it is affected by a force, for example by the wind.

example.ex: Blond strands of hair whipped in the wind.

value.def: If someone whips something out or whips it off, they take it out or take it off very quickly and suddenly.

example.tran: 鲍勃迅速掏出他的笔记本。

example.ex: Players were whipping their shirts off...
example.tran: 运动员们在飞快地脱衬衫。

example.ex: My waitress whipped the plate away and put down my bill.
example.tran: 我的服务员麻利地撤走盘子并搁下我的账单。

value.def: If something or someone whips somewhere, they move there or go there very quickly.

example.ex: The wind out here is whipping along at about 30 miles an hour...
example.tran: 在这里，大风以每小时大约30英里的速度刮着。

example.ex: I whipped into a parking space.
example.tran: 我迅速地驶入一个停车位。

value.def: When you whip something liquid such as cream or an egg, you stir it very fast until it is thick or stiff.

example.tran: 搅打奶油直到它变黏稠。

example.ex: Whip the eggs, oils and honey together.
example.tran: 把鸡蛋、油和蜂蜜搅打在一起。

value.def: If you whip people into an emotional state, you deliberately cause and encourage them to be in that state.

example.ex: He could whip a crowd into hysteria...
example.tran: 他能让一群人变得歇斯底里。

example.ex: Politicians and businessmen have whipped themselves into a panic.
example.tran: 政治家和商人们把他们自己弄得十分恐慌。

value.def: A whip is a member of a political party in a parliament or legislature who is responsible for making sure that party members are present to vote on important issues and that they vote in the appropriate way.
value.tran: 组织秘书，党鞭（维持党纪并督导该党议员出席议会重要议题的讨论和表决的人）

value.def: If you have the whip hand, you have power over someone else in a particular situation.

example.ex: These days the shopper has the whip hand, and will not buy if stores fail to lower their prices.
example.tran: 如今购物者占主导地位，如果商店不降价，他们是不会买的。

trans: 激起，煽动（仇恨等危险情感）
